  DIRL [Dn:][path>][filename] ..

Low Memory

Lists specified files in drive Dn:,
path and specified pattern of file
names. If no file name pattern is
specified then all files will be
listed.

In difference to the command DIR the
header with volume/directory name and
the free sector count at the end are
not displayed. Furthermore protected
files and directories are marked with
the character * in front of the name
and the change time is diplayed
including seconds.
